Hold on one second.

25:02.918 --> 25:04.088
I'm gonna see if I can...

25:04.089 --> 25:05.929
I can see
if I can calm him down.

25:12.094 --> 25:14.762
You know,
so, like, he's like,

25:14.763 --> 25:16.764
leaning back
and eating a sandwich.

25:16.765 --> 25:19.392
And he's got, you know,
a magazine in his lap.

25:19.393 --> 25:22.520
And as he stands up
to greet them,

25:22.521 --> 25:23.943
he, like, throws it down.

25:23.944 --> 25:26.107
And if you look at"
look at...

25:26.108 --> 25:28.401
look at it, you know,
close up,

25:28.402 --> 25:32.989
it's an actual
Playgirl magazine.

25:32.990 --> 25:36.369
Yeah, a Playgirl magazine
in the lobby of a hotel

25:36.370 --> 25:39.120
right in front of his boss,
like on his first day at work.

25:41.457 --> 25:42.999
Yeah.

25:43.000 --> 25:46.800
Like, the cover is like, people
getting ready for New Year's.

25:46.801 --> 25:49.297
There's an article about incest.

25:49.298 --> 25:52.846
At the beginning of the film,
Danny's been physically abused.

25:52.847 --> 25:54.095
But there's a suggestion

25:54.096 --> 25:56.643
that he's been
sexually abused as well.

25:59.725 --> 26:02.935
You know, so like,
just in that one...

26:02.936 --> 26:09.567
one shot, there's all these,
like, you know, complex things

26:09.568 --> 26:10.863
going on in the background,

26:10.864 --> 26:13.157
like things
that are choreographed

26:13.158 --> 26:14.498
to match up exactly.

26:14.499 --> 26:16.240
Like, we see a guy...

26:16.241 --> 26:20.161
we see a guy, carrying a...

26:20.162 --> 26:25.833
entering the room,
carrying a rug.

26:25.834 --> 26:28.506
And by the time
the scene is just ending,

26:28.507 --> 26:30.598
we see him
walking up the stairs.

26:30.599 --> 26:35.051
Like, he's crossed
the entire place,

26:35.052 --> 26:36.052
you know, timed exactly.

26:36.053 --> 26:37.053
I don't even...

26:40.599 --> 26:41.600
Yeah.

26:48.524 --> 26:51.651
- When Ullman
is leading the Torrances

26:51.652 --> 26:55.738
out of the elevator
and into the Colorado Lounge

26:55.739 --> 27:01.035
for the first time,
there's a pile of suitcases.

27:01.036 --> 27:03.955
And in the dissolve
into that scene,

27:03.956 --> 27:08.417
the scene before,
a group of tourists

27:08.418 --> 27:09.757
are standing in the lobby.

27:09.758 --> 27:13.007
And those tourists
dissolve into the suitcases.

27:13.008 --> 27:15.179
Now, as an historian
of the Holocaust,

27:15.180 --> 27:17.844
I find that
very, very striking

27:17.845 --> 27:19.222
and certainly not accidental

27:19.223 --> 27:22.682
'cause he's using those
sort of cross-dissolves.

27:22.683 --> 27:25.104
Now, that could be,
along with the ladder,

27:25.105 --> 27:27.821
where he's trying to make
substantive connections

27:27.822 --> 27:29.531
as well as formal ones.

27:36.405 --> 27:37.907
- Oh, the window
in Ullman's office,

27:37.908 --> 27:39.954
it is absolutely beautiful.

27:42.244 --> 27:43.712
The casual viewer
isn't going to see

27:43.713 --> 27:46.372
so many things
in Kubrick's films,

27:46.373 --> 27:49.377
although I think they may
register unconsciously.

27:49.378 --> 27:51.297
You know, but they're not
going to, you know,

27:51.298 --> 27:52.759
perceive
perhaps these things

27:52.760 --> 27:53.926
because as I've said,

27:53.927 --> 27:56.966
he presents them
as being real.

27:56.967 --> 27:58.262
You know, it's realism.

27:58.263 --> 28:00.011
And it's not
your typical horror...

28:00.012 --> 28:01.264
you don't have a horror film

28:01.265 --> 28:03.311
except for this one section
at the end,

28:03.312 --> 28:07.643
right where Wendy walks in
and the lobby is blue

28:07.644 --> 28:09.315
and you've got the cobwebs
all around.

28:09.316 --> 28:10.483
And it's almost like

28:10.484 --> 28:12.401
a Saturday morning
kind of horror film

28:12.402 --> 28:13.946
suddenly there for a second.

28:13.947 --> 28:15.401
And you kind of go.

28:15.402 --> 28:18.743
"Ooh, what is this with
the skeletons and the cobwebs?"

28:18.744 --> 28:20.284
And it's kind of cheesy.

28:20.285 --> 28:22.829
But then, after that,
following that,

28:22.830 --> 28:25.122
you've got her going down
the red hallway,

28:25.123 --> 28:26.667
which...
on the big screen,

28:26.668 --> 28:28.289
that's petrifying.

28:28.290 --> 28:30.509
So I think the kind of
cheesiness before it

28:30.510 --> 28:32.628
helps set up
that red hallway.

28:35.047 --> 28:37.131
So anyway, what was I saying?

28:37.132 --> 28:38.304
Right, the windows.

28:38.305 --> 28:40.468
So you got... Jack has entered.

28:40.469 --> 28:42.392
And you can see...
you are...

28:42.393 --> 28:43.804
Kubrick shows you.

28:43.805 --> 28:46.900
But he shows you this lobby,
and you get to see...

28:46.901 --> 28:51.103
as Jack moves across the lobby,
you see the elevator beyond.

28:51.104 --> 28:53.150
And you see beyond that,
a hallway.

28:53.151 --> 28:56.364
You don't see yet how far back
it goes, you know,

28:56.365 --> 28:59.364
the other things back there,
but you have an impression

28:59.365 --> 29:02.829
that this place is towards
the middle of the hotel.

29:02.830 --> 29:04.997
You just have that
impression that it's towards

29:04.998 --> 29:06.661
the middle of the hotel.

29:06.662 --> 29:10.212
And you go from the lobby into
the general manager's office

29:10.213 --> 29:15.419
and then into Ullman's office,
and there's this window.

29:15.420 --> 29:17.341
And the window's
a powerful window.

29:17.342 --> 29:19.717
I mean, the light coming
through there is glaring.

29:19.718 --> 29:22.093
It's like a character in itself.

29:22.094 --> 29:24.220
It takes over.

29:24.221 --> 29:27.687
And you've got these tendril-y,
sinister kind of trees

29:27.688 --> 29:29.060
that are outside the window.

29:29.061 --> 29:30.685
And you've got...

29:30.686 --> 29:32.357
it's just such
a forceful presence,

29:32.358 --> 29:34.072
this light
that comes over everything.

29:34.073 --> 29:36.065
And, you know...

29:36.066 --> 29:39.026
And there's
something wrong with it.

29:39.027 --> 29:40.199
There's something wrong with it,

29:40.200 --> 29:42.822
and I think it registers
as something wrong.

29:42.823 --> 29:44.496
This is an impossible window.

29:44.497 --> 29:46.784
It's not... it is impossible.

29:46.785 --> 29:48.205
It is physically impossible.

29:48.206 --> 29:49.203
It cannot be there.

29:49.204 --> 29:50.705
It should not be there.

29:50.706 --> 29:54.709
There's no place in the hotel
for this window to exist.

29:54.710 --> 29:55.710
It's only toward...

29:55.711 --> 29:57.179
finally,
towards the end of the film,

29:57.180 --> 30:00.548
that you have the realization
that there are several hallways

30:00.549 --> 30:04.218
in succession behind the office.

30:04.219 --> 30:06.971
You see it when Wendy,

30:06.972 --> 30:10.146
when she's later down there and
she sees Dick Hallorann's body

30:10.147 --> 30:11.934
after he's been killed.

30:11.935 --> 30:16.190
You have her behind... in that
hallway behind the office.

30:19.651 --> 30:22.323
So really, now, what
can I tell you about the maps?

